I haven't been able to do more than glance over this (my eyes are tired, and I'll probably read it tomorrow), but I'd just like to say that I really liked that you've mixed the format up a bit by putting inscriptions, etc. in a box near the start of the description. It's a nice change from the standard 'lengthy inscriptions go at the end, in an addendum' set-up most articles go with. It's a good reminder that the SCP format is a format, not a formula, and that there's no real reason to rigidly adhere to some of the common article-writing conventions.







